The '''A340''' is a major road in the south of [[England]], portions of which are known as the Aldermaston Road, Tadley Hill, Basingstoke Road and Tidmarsh Road.

==Route==
Starting in the south of [[Basingstoke]], [[Hampshire]], it runs west, forming the western side of the Basingstoke ringroad, before swinging north to [[Tadley]] and then enters [[Berkshire]].  It passes the gates of the [[Atomic Weapons Establishment]] at [[Aldermaston]], before passing through the village of Aldermaston itself and then joining the [[A4 road (Great Britain)|A4]] at [[Aldermaston Wharf]]. After approximately {{Convert|2.5|mi|km}} north-east, the A340 runs further north to [[Pangbourne]], to the west of [[Reading, Berkshire|Reading]]. This section of the road is thought to follow the Roman road from [[Calleva Atrebatum]] (about {{Convert|7|mi|km}} to the south).

