The '''A688''' is a [[road]] in [[County Durham]] in [[North East England]].

It begins at the junction with the [[A67 road]] in [[Barnard Castle]] and continues in a north easterly direction for {{convert|25|mi|km}}, terminating at the A181 to the east of [[Durham, England|Durham]] City.

The road passes through the village of [[Staindrop]], past [[Raby Castle]] through [[West Auckland]], [[Bishop Auckland]] and on to [[Spennymoor]]. It then continues through the [[Thinford]] intersection with the [[A167]] to Junction 61 of the [[A1(M)]] at [[Bowburn]]. The latest extension to the road from the A1(M) to the A181 was opened on 30 October 2008.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.thenorthernecho.co.uk/news/3806648.Minister_opens_new___11_4m_road_link/| title=Minister opens new £11.4m road link between Wheatley Hill and Bowburn | publisher=The Northern Echo| date=2008-10-30| accessdate=2008-11-04}}</ref>

The road is single-carriageway except for a short {{convert|800|m|yd|abbr=on}} stretch of [[dual-carriageway]] at Spennymoor.

