'''Bakata''' was the capital of the [[Ahom kingdom]]<ref>https://books.google.com/books/about/Capitals_of_Ahom_Kingdom.html?id=DAvhbwAACAAJ&redir_esc=y</ref> (present-day [[Assam]], [[Northeast India]]) established by the [[Ahom Dynasty|Ahom king]] [[Suhungmung]]. Since this capital was by the [[Dihing river]], Suhungmung is also known as the ''Dihingia Raja''. The next king, Suklenmung, moved the capital to [[Garhgaon]].

