{{Orphan|date=August 2015}}

[[File:Morne à Craie.JPG|thumb| Morne à Craie]]
'''Morne à Craie''' is a mountain on the island of [[Terre-de-Haut]] in the archipelago of the [[Îles des Saintes]] in [[Guadeloupe]]. It has an altitude of {{convert|148|m}}.<ref name="ClercClerc1963">{{cite book|last1=Clerc|first1=Maurice|last2=Clerc|first2=Jacqueline|title=Antilles-Guyanes: Circuit des Caraïbes|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Ro8XAAAAIAAJ|year=1963|publisher=Hachette|language=French|page=212}}</ref>
The south side of the mountain is a classified natural area of ecological interest for its flora and fauna, and was acquired in 2003 by the Conservatoire du Littoral.

