The '''Wyoming Basin [[United States physiographic region#Rocky Mountain Section|physiographic province]]''' is a geographic area through which the [[Continental Divide of the Americas]] traverses. The province includes the [[Washakie Basin]]<ref name=wsgs>{{cite web|title=Select Area of Interest |url=http://www.wsgs.uwyo.edu/StratWeb/indexmap/indexmap.aspx |work=[Wyoming Stratigraphy] |publisher=Wyoming State Geological Survey |accessdate=2010-04-24}} ([http://www.wsgs.uwyo.edu/StratWeb/GreatDivideBasin/Default.aspx Great Basin Divide], [http://www.wsgs.uwyo.edu/StratWeb/WashakieBasin/Default.aspx Washakie Basin])</ref> and [[Great Divide Basin]]s, and is demarcated by the following: <!--SOURCE: File:US west coast physiographic regions map.jpg (ALONG WITH THE FOLLOWING):--> *southwest: [[Uinta Mountains]]<!--SOURCE: File:Greenutrivermap.png--> *west: west side of [[Green River (Colorado River)|Green River]] watershed<!--SOURCE: File:Greenutrivermap.png-->
